{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Mode one requires the model to select the most appropriate option from several answer options.",
    "RACE (Lai et al, 2017) and DREAM (Sun et al, 2019) are specifically selected from English exams designed by human experts, requiring the model to answer multiplechoice questions about the content of given English articles.",
    "Similarly, C 3 (Sun et al, 2020) and ReClor (Yu et al, 2020b) are extracted from corresponding Chinese exams and graduate entrance exams, respectively, each containing relevant multiple-choice questions.",
    "Mode two involves judging the correctness of a question using either \"Yes\" or \"No.\"",
    "BoolQ (Clark et al, 2019) requires the model to respond with \"Yes\" or \"No\" to complex inquiries and non-factual information."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "RACE (Lai et al, 2017) and DREAM (Sun et al, 2019) are specifically selected from English exams designed by human experts, requiring the model to answer multiplechoice questions about the content of given English articles.",
    "Similarly, C 3 (Sun et al, 2020) and ReClor (Yu et al, 2020b) are extracted from corresponding Chinese exams and graduate entrance exams, respectively, each containing relevant multiple-choice questions.",
    "BoolQ (Clark et al, 2019) requires the model to respond with \"Yes\" or \"No\" to complex inquiries and non-factual information."
  ]
